  <description type="morphology">Leaves 1–3(–5) cm, ultimate lobes narrowly oblong to spatulate or linear, ultimate margins entire or serrate (teeth apiculate). Phyl-laries: abaxial faces sericeous to arachnose, margins often ciliolate. Paleae 4–5 mm (including spinose tips). Ray laminae yellow, 6–12+ mm. Disc corollas 3.5–4 mm. Cypselae 1.8–2.2 mm; pappi usually 2–2.5 mm. 2n = 18.</description>
  <description type="phenology">Flowering Jul–Sep.</description>
